title: Van Allen Probes/RPS Level 2 Data - J. Mazur (The Aerospace Corporation)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/rbsp/rbspa/l2/rps/psbr-rps/2012/rbspa_l2_psbr-rps_20120902_v3.0.0.cdf. The most common cadence, 253 [ms] = PT0.253S, occurred for 99.9146% of the 340504 timesteps.

parameters.name: MET_SEC
parameters.description: MET at mid-point of sector

parameters.name: Mission_Day
parameters.description: Mission day of level 0 files for this data point

parameters.name: Position
parameters.description: Spacecraft Position (GEO)

parameters.name: Position_Quality
parameters.description: Position quality flag: 0 - definitive, 1 - predicted

parameters.name: Attitude_Quality
parameters.description: Attitude quality flag: 0 - definitive, 1 - quick-look, 2 - predicted

parameters.name: Orbit_Number
parameters.description: Orbit number

parameters.name: Orbit_Status
parameters.description: Orbit status: 0 = outbound, 1 = inbound

parameters.name: Orbit_Epoch
parameters.description: Decimal hours since perigee

parameters.name: EarthRadialAngle
parameters.description: Angle of incidence of particle coming from center of Earth (relative to normal incidence)

parameters.name: EarthConeAngle
parameters.description: Half-angle of Earth as seen from Spacecraft

parameters.name: B_Meas
parameters.description: Measured magnetic field vector in GEO

parameters.name: B_Meas_Flag
parameters.description: Source of Measured field - 0 indicates MAG L0 file, 1 indicates MAG L1 file, etc. If 255, then the OPQ77 model field is used for computing Alpha and Beta

parameters.name: BORE_SIGHT
parameters.description: RPS bore sight vector in GEO (parallel to incoming normally incident particle)

parameters.name: SPIN_OMEGA
parameters.description: RPS spin axis vector in GEO vector norm is spin rate

parameters.name: DATA_CHANNEL_COUNTS
parameters.description: Counts in data channels based on EVENT_ENERGY_MIN2SSD

parameters.description: RMS error in ln(FPDU) including Poisson and FPDU_Crosscalib_RMSE

parameters.name: FPDU_Quality
parameters.description: Quality flag for FPDU fluxes: 0 - highest quality, 1 - problem with time resolution (less than 5% live time in sector), 2 - contamination, 3 - saturation, 4 - other problem, 5 - possible electron background, 10 -not yet quality checked

title: Van Allen Probes/RPS Level 2 Data - J. Mazur (The Aerospace Corporation)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'EVENT_Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/rbsp/rbspa/l2/rps/psbr-rps/2012/rbspa_l2_psbr-rps_20120902_v3.0.0.cdf. The most common cadence, 16 [ms] = PT0.016S, occurred for 1.4199% of the 2405 timesteps.

parameters.name: Time
parameters.x_description: UTC of event to 1/64 second resolution

parameters.name: EVENT_MET
parameters.description: MET of event, combination of Packet's MET_SEC and  EVENT_SUBTIME_CODE

parameters.name: EVENT_Mission_Day
parameters.description: Mission day of level 0 files for this data point

parameters.name: EVENT_Position
parameters.description: Spacecraft Position (GEO)

parameters.name: EVENT_Orbit_Number
parameters.description: Orbit number

parameters.name: EVENT_Orbit_Status
parameters.description: Orbit status: 0 = outbound, 1 = inbound

parameters.name: EVENT_Orbit_Epoch
parameters.description: Decimal hours since perigee

parameters.name: EVENT_L90
parameters.description: McIlwain L of locally mirroring particle in OPQ

parameters.name: EVENT_L
parameters.description: McIlwain L of incoming particle along RPS boresight axis

parameters.name: EVENT_MLT
parameters.description: Magnetic local time (OPQ)

parameters.name: EVENT_Alpha
parameters.description: Pitch angle of incoming particle along RPS boresight axis

parameters.name: EVENT_Beta
parameters.description: Gyrophase angle of incoming particle along RPS boresight axis (zero when heading away from Earth)

parameters.name: EVENT_B_Mirror
parameters.description: Magnetic field strength at mirror point for incoming particle along RPS boresight axis

parameters.name: EVENT_Alpha_Eq
parameters.description: Equatorial pitch angle (OPQ) of incoming particle along RPS boresight axis

parameters.name: EVENT_PULSEHEIGHTS
parameters.description: D1-D9 detector pulse heights

parameters.name: EVENT_ENERGY_DEPOSIT
parameters.description: D1-D8 Energy Deposit

parameters.name: EVENT_D9_COULOMBS
parameters.description: Coulombs deposited in MCP behind Cherenkov Radiator

parameters.name: EVENT_CHE_PHOTONS
parameters.description: Photons collected in Cherenkov Radiator

parameters.name: EVENT_DIRECTION
parameters.description: 0 - forward, 1 - backward

parameters.name: EVENT_ENERGY
parameters.description: Estimated event energy (uses EVENT_ENERGY_MIN2SSD)

parameters.name: EVENT_ENERGY_MIN2SSD
parameters.description: Estimated event energy using the average of minimum 2 SSD deposits algorithm

parameters.name: EVENT_ENERGY_SSDA
parameters.description: Estimated event energy using SSD average algorithm

parameters.name: EVENT_ENERGY_CHE
parameters.description: Estimated event energy using the Cherenkov light only

parameters.name: EVENT_SIGMA_E
parameters.description: Standard error of ln(EVENT_ENERGY)

parameters.name: EVENT_CHANNEL_ID
parameters.description: ID number of data channel to which the particle is assigned

parameters.name: EVENT_TYPE
parameters.description: Event classification (-1:INVALID, 0:UNKNOWN, 1:PEN, 2:CHE, 3:ALPHA mode, 127:FILL)
